cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the problem of dataset bias in computer vision, which is a common issue in the field of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning architectures (cs.LG) and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) (cs.AI) for image analysis. Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of existing debiasing methods (cs.CL) and the limitations of generalization of learning methods (cs.CR).
